article.headline: Dayton 71, Duquesne 60
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Norman Plummer and Brian Roberts scored 12 points each and Trent Meacham added 11 as Dayton beat Duquesne 71-60 on Saturday. The Flyers outrebounded the Dukes 46-34 and hit 25 of 34 free throws to win their third in a row. Dayton suffered a double-overtime home loss to the Dukes on Jan. 5. Dayton (9-5, 2-1 Atlantic 10) led 35-22 at halftime, taking advantage of a slow start by Duquesne. The Dukes shot 25.9 from the field in the first half. Duquesne (4-13, 1-3), which has lost all three of its games since playing Dayton, twice cut into the Flyers' lead in the second half. The Dukes went on a 10-2 run to close 49-43 with 10:21 remaining and the score was 57-51 with 3:43 left. But Dayton pushed the lead back to double digits on a 3-point shot by Marques Bennett, his first attempt of the game, giving the Flyers a 64-54 lead with 1:35 remaining. Kieron Achara led Duquesne with 16 points. Jack Higgins scored 10.
